appliesTo: LICENSE
purpose: The MIT license text — a single-page legal artifact, not documentation.
owner: governance
created: 2026-07-10
---

# Rule: LICENSE

`LICENSE` carries the MIT license text verbatim. It is treated as a `.md`
file by `bun run check:md` only because it shares the extension. There is
no structural requirement beyond "the MIT text, end-to-end, with copyright
year/holder that matches the repo owner".

If the project relicenses, write a new `LICENSE`, add a memory retro for
the relicensing event, and update this rule to point at the new path (the
rule file stays; its purpose statement gets a `supersedes:` line).
